# Testing Rules

## Framework
Unit + Integration: Vitest
E2E: Playwright
Component: Storybook (optional, for UI-heavy components)

## Test File Location
Co-locate unit tests: src/lib/ai/agents/job-analyst.test.ts
E2E tests in: e2e/ directory at root

## What Requires Tests

### Unit tests (Vitest)
- Every agent function in src/lib/ai/agents/
- Every chunking strategy in src/lib/rag/chunking/
- Every Zod schema (valid + invalid inputs)
- Match scoring logic

### Integration tests (Vitest)
- API routes: mock Supabase + mock Anthropic, test request/response
- Trigger.dev jobs: test the job logic with mocked external services

### E2E tests (Playwright)
- Full generation flow: upload CV → paste job → generate → review → (don't submit)
- Auth flow: sign-up → sign-in → protected route
- Upload flow: drag-and-drop → extraction status → embedded confirmation

## Mocking Strategy
- Mock Anthropic SDK: return fixture responses from src/__mocks__/
- Mock Supabase: use Supabase's local dev stack (supabase start)
- Mock Pinecone: jest/vitest mock returning fixture embeddings
- Mock Voyage AI: return deterministic vectors for test chunks

## Agent Test Pattern
```typescript
describe('JobAnalystAgent', () => {
  it('extracts required skills from job description', async () => {
    const mockClaude = vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(fixtureJobAnalysis)
    const result = await runJobAnalyst({ rawJobDescription: fixtures.jobJD }, mockTrace)
    expect(result.mustHaveSkills).toContain('TypeScript')
    expect(result.seniority).toBe('senior')
  })
  
  it('handles malformed LLM response with retry', async () => {
    // First call returns garbage, second returns valid JSON
  })
})
```

## Coverage Requirements
Agent functions: 80% line coverage minimum
API routes: happy path + auth failure + validation failure covered
RAG retrieval: test with empty results, single result, full results
